Second task for https://github.com/openaddresses/openaddresses-ops/issues/7: use [attribution tag](https://github.com/openaddresses/openaddresses/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#optional-tags) to populate a new boolean value for required attribution, and provide for explicit attribution settings by borrowing terminology from [CC namespace](https://creativecommons.org/ns). Add a True/False/Null output attribution field.

Explicit attribution requirement:

    {
        "license": {
            "attribution": true,
            "attribution name": "Joe Blow"
        }
    }

Equivalent implicit attribution:

    {
        "attribution": "Joe Blow"
    }

Missing license:attribution should be interpreted as True, so this is also equivalent:

    {
        "license": {
            "attribution name": "Joe Blow"
        }
    }

Completely omitted attribution information should be interpreted as False, equivalent to:

    {
        "license": {
            "attribution": false
        }
    }

Notebook (4.0.4) seems to serialize the session identifier (which, according to the doc, is a UUID) differently than the console (4.0.3). While the console sends a standard canonical UUID in the form 8-4-4-4-12 the notebook send a all uppercase 32-bit string without hyphens. UUIDs cannot thus not be parsed as such and need to be treated as strings which seems just plain wrong to me.UUIDs should always be exchanged in their canonical form.

